Limelight->Environment

Environment... is the next selection in the Limelight menu. When
selected, it brings up the Environment Editor.

The Environment Editor is used to edit the global attributes of the
environment in Movieola. This environment will affect all other
lighting elements as might be expected in a real world context. You
might think of it like this, if you selected "Fog" then all elements
of lighting in the environment will have the "Fog" effect imparted to
them.

The Environment Editor consist of the following tools and options:

